    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3; this gap is accepted on the basis that the single ASTM F1717 test condition is the regulatory standard condition and that the model risk level 3 / Medium assurance level does not mandate multi-condition testing for this device class. All three primary QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria (QoI difference < 10%, E/uval < 1.96). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible to support the 510(k) submission.",
